summary: Tilen Lebar (b. 1993) is a Slovenian composer, an improviser and a saxophonist based in The Hague, the Netherlands. After finishing his studies at Conservatoire for Music and Ballet in Maribor with Peter Kruder, he has continued and successfully completed a Bachelorâ€™s Degree in musical arts with principal study in saxophone class of Matjaz Drevensek at the Academy of Music, University in Ljubljana.  Further on, he continued his Master's Instrumental pedagogical studies in Saxophone under Miha Rogina and Matjaz Drevensek at the same University. Later on, he was educating himself in the composition class of Uros Rojko at the Academy of Music, University of Ljubljana. Tilen continued his Master Composition studies at Royal Conservatoire in The Hague in the classes of Guus Janssen, Peter Adriaansz and Cornelis De Bondt. Moreover, he continued his saxophone studies in class of Raaf Hekkema. He is actively enrolled in the field of chamber music, as well as is regularly premiering new works of young composers. Furthermore, Tilen is actively participating in the field of improvised music scene and interdisciplinary arts and regularly cooperates with Zavod Sploh, KUD Mreza, Ensemble Szene Instrumental, CONA | institute for contemporary arts processing and Inexhaustible Editions. His sound world reveals a great knowledge of individual instrumental extended techniques as well as contemplated colours, detailed structures in sound tinctures, all of those expressing in his personal view in introverted musical approach. His works were performed in Slovenia, Estonia, Austria, Germany, Italy, Switzerland, Croatia and The Netherlands. His collaborations included ensemble Asamisimasa from Oslo, ensemble Stere (Slovenia), ensemble Oerknal (The Netherlands), Slagwerk Den Haag, Experimental studio of SWR Freiburg and Dutch National Opera & Ballet, among others. He was a recipient of a scholarship by the Ministry of Culture Republic of Slovenia for his postgraduate studies at Royal Conservatoire in The Hague. Since 2019 he is an active member of Society of Slovene Composers (DSS).
